title: Sautéed Bass With Mint Pesto And Spiced Carrots
summary: Sautéed Bass With Mint Pesto And Spiced Carrots might be just the main course you are searching for. This caveman, gluten free, dairy free, and primal recipe serves 4 and costs $4.46 per serving. One portion of this dish contains around 34g of protein, 22g of fat, and a total of 388 calories. This recipe from Love and Olive Oil has 1 fans. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 45 minutes. If you have lemon juice, cumin seeds, extra virgin olive oil, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 85%. This score is tremendous. Similar recipes are Sauteed Striped Bass with Mint Pesto and Spiced Carrots, Spiced Beef Stew with Carrots and Mint, and Spiced Lamb Chops on Sauteed Peppers and Onions with Garlic and Mint Couscous.
instructions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add carrots, crushed red pepper, and ground seeds; saut until carrots begin to brown in spots, about 5 minutes. Add broth and lemon juice and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until carrots are tender, about 6 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in each of 2 large nonstick skillets over medium-high heat. Add fish and cook until browned on both sides and just opaque in center, about 5 minutes total.Divide carrots and any juices among 4 plates. Top each serving with 1 fish fillet.
